thread 'main' (11638) panicked at /home/ubuntu/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/minus-5.6.1/src/core/mod.rs:48:9:
CommandQueue::push_back() caled when  RUNMODE is not set. This is most likely a bug. Please report the issue on minus's issue tracker on Github.
note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace

The panic is caused by `pager.follow_output(true)` — that method pushes a command onto an internal queue that only exists once the pager's run-loop has started. Calling it *before* `page_all` runs violates minus's internal invariant.

The minimal fix is to remove that call. But `minus` is also just extra dependency weight here; spawning the system pager (respecting `$PAGER`, falling back to `less`/`more`) is simpler and more robust:

```rust
// src/main.rs  — replace the page_output function and remove the minus dep

fn page_output(text: &str) {
    use std::io::Write;
    use std::process::{Command, Stdio};

    if !std::io::stdout().is_terminal() {
        print!("{}", text);
        return;
    }

    // Honour $PAGER; try less, then more, then plain print.
    let candidates: Vec<String> = {
        let mut v = Vec::new();
        if let Ok(p) = std::env::var("PAGER") {
            v.push(p);
        }
        v.push("less".into());
        v.push("more".into());
        v
    };

    for pager in &candidates {
        // `less -R` passes ANSI escapes through; ignore the flag for other pagers.
        let mut cmd = Command::new(pager);
        if pager == "less" {
            cmd.arg("-R");
        }
        cmd.stdin(Stdio::piped());

        if let Ok(mut child) = cmd.spawn() {
            if let Some(mut stdin) = child.stdin.take() {
                // Ignore broken-pipe — user may have quit the pager early.
                let _ = stdin.write_all(text.as_bytes());
            }
            let _ = child.wait();
            return;
        }
    }

    // No pager available — just print.
    println!("{}", text);
}
```

Then remove `minus` from `Cargo.toml`:

```toml
# Cargo.toml — remove this line
